<pdd-reason>Exposes evidence policy enforcement under the checkup command group with an optional advisory LLM pass.</pdd-reason>

<pdd-interface>
{
  "type": "module",
  "module": {
    "functions": [
      {"name": "gate_cmd", "description": "Evaluate evidence policy gate via pdd checkup gate with optional advisory LLM pass"}
    ]
  }
}
</pdd-interface>

<pdd-dependency>gate_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_advisory_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<pdd-dependency>commands/checkup_review_options_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>

% Write `pdd/commands/gate.py`, Click CLI for ``pdd checkup gate``.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Public API
- `gate_cmd` Click command: `pdd checkup gate [TARGET] [--policy PATH] [--stories-dir PATH] [--tests-dir PATH] [--json] [--review off|explain]`

% Behavior
- `TARGET` omitted: evaluate all `.pdd/evidence/devunits/*.latest.json` under the project root.
- `TARGET` basename: evaluate one dev unit's latest manifest.
- `TARGET` path ending in `.latest.json`: evaluate that manifest file.
- Exit 0 on pass, 1 on failure; `--json` emits structured `GateResult`.
- Wire `--review off|explain` (default `off`) using the `review_option` decorator from `pdd.commands.checkup_review_options`.
- Compute the deterministic exit code before any LLM advisory call; the advisory pass MUST NOT alter the exit code.
- When `--review explain` is set: call the advisory LLM pass after gate evaluation; on any exception set `advisory.status="failed"` and continue; inject `"advisory": report_as_dict(advisory_report)` as a top-level sibling key in the JSON dict; in non-JSON mode print a brief advisory summary to stderr.
- When `--review off` (default): output is unchanged.
- Import `SKIPPED_REPORT`, `failed_report`, `final_exit_code`, `report_as_dict` from `pdd.checkup_advisory`.

% Code output
- Code: `pdd/commands/gate.py`
